# Manzel — Real Estate Management / ERP

This is a **Management/ERP application** for multi-building property, facility, and HOA operations. It is NOT a marketing site or simple CRUD demo.

## Product context
- Unit-centric data model: ownership, tenancy, and management periods must be queryable at any historical date.
- Three service lines: Property Management, Facility Management, HOA (optional).
- Multi-entity: management company, facility entity, per-HOA books.
- Desktop-first productivity UI; fully functional on tablet and mobile.

## Coding standards

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always on. No `any` except documented escape hatches.
- Domain types live in `/types`. API shapes and DB models must not leak into UI without mapping.
- Prefer discriminated unions for workflow states (lease status, work order status).

### Architecture
- App Router: server components by default; `"use client"` only for interactivity.
- `/components/ui` — presentational primitives only (shadcn).
- `/components/layout` — dashboard shell (header, sidebar, entity switcher).
- `/lib` — pure utilities, server actions, API clients. No JSX in utility modules.
- Feature logic colocated under route segments or `/lib/modules/{property|facility|hoa}`.
- Financial and audit actions require explicit audit logging hooks.

### UI/UX
- Match template aesthetic: slate neutrals, blue primary, dark header bar, bordered sidebar.
- Data-dense layouts: tables, KPI cards, monospace figures for currency.
- Use Framer Motion (`motion`) for subtle page/section transitions — never flashy.
- Responsive: design at `lg+` first; sidebar collapses to sheet on `< lg`; tables scroll horizontally on mobile.

### Performance
- Paginate/virtualize large tables. Avoid loading full portfolio in client state.
- Use `loading.tsx` and Suspense boundaries per route segment.
- Images via `next/image`. Charts lazy-loaded.

### Security
- RBAC per service line. Never trust client-side role checks alone.
- All mutations validated with Zod (or equivalent) on the server.

### Do not
- Add marketing landing pages to this repo.
- Mix HOA funds with management company books.
- Skip date-range validation on ownership/tenancy/management period records.
